e commands  " }{TEXT 258 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 6 " and  " }{TEXT 259 8 
"simplify" }{TEXT -1 298 "  can be used to rearrange and manipulate al
gebraic sums and products of polynomial expressions.  Go back to each \+
of your calculations of a., b., c. and d. and add to each line a comma
nd to expand the calculation and a command to simplify the caclulation
.  E.g.,  the line for a. would change from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 1 " " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 4 "f*g;" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,(*$)%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"F)*$)F'\"\"#F)!\"\"*&F,F)
F'F)F-F),**&\"\"'F)F&F)F)*&\"#6F)F+F)F)*&F1F)F'F)F)F)F)F)" }}}{PARA 0 
