0 "" {TEXT -1 17 "Note the effect  " }{TEXT 262 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 
5 " and " }{TEXT 263 8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 42 "  have on the way the \+
calculation appears." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 284 173 "
In the first line it simply writes the problems. It will do the add an
d subtract. The second line multiplies and divides the problem.  The t
hird line simplifies the problem." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The Maple commands " }{TEXT 260 16 "expan
d, simplify" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 261 6 "normal" }{TEXT -1 483 "
 can be use to rearrange, manipulate and simplify (cancel common facto
rs) algebraic sums, products and quotients of rational expressions.   \+
When a rational expression is normalized, any common factors are cance
lled.  Go back to each of your calculations of e., f., g., h. and i. a
nd add to each line a command to expand the calculation, to normalize \+
the calculation, to simplify the calculation and both expand and norma
lize the calculation.  E.g., the line for e. would change from:" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
6 "F*H/G;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&*$)%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"F)
