" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 271 "3.  Fundamen
tal Theorem of Algebra.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra asserts th
at every non-constant polynomial (with complex-valued coefficients) ha
s a root (a zero, a solution).  A consequence of the Fundamental Theor
em of Algebra is that every polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 270 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 13 " has exactly " }{TEXT 271 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 108 " roots.  A
n alternate formulation of this consequence would be that every non-co
nstant polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 273 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 38 " can be f
actored into a product of a  " }{TEXT 272 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 16 " linear \+
factors." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
35 "Consider the following polynomials:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 
"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "I.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "f := x^3-x^2-
2*x" "6#>%\"fG,(*$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*$F'\"\"#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT 
-1 4 "    " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 23 "     II.               " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 25 "  III.                   " }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "IV.
    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "F := x^4-144" "6#>%\"FG,&*$%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"\"$W
\"!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 12 "            " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 " V.
    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "G := 3*x^4+4*x^3-2*x^2+x-6;" "6#>%\"GG,,*&\"\"$
\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"%F(F(*&F+F(*$F*F'F(F(*&\"\"#F(*$F*F/F(!\"\"F*F(\"\"'F
1" }{TEXT -1 9 "         " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "VI.   " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "H := x^5-x^2-2*x" "6#>%\"HG,(*$%\"xG\"\"&\"\"\"*$F'\"\"
#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 24 "                        " }}{PARA 0 
